Linux systems enables additional permission (standard: read, write, execute).

To enable writing and disable deleting for users which are not owners:
chmod a+t file

There is catalogue catalogueX and its group is GROUP_A. To automatically set GROUP_A to all files inside catalogue catalogueX:
chmod g+t catalogueX

There is a file with owner ownerX. To enable anyone to execute this file with ownerX permissions:
chmod u+s file
